# PostService

Rust microservice for creating and retrieving photo/video posts tagged to Michelin restaurants. Writes denormalized copies to three Cassandra tables for efficient list queries, and publishes MQTT events consumed by FeedService and StatsService.

---

## Architecture

```
Client
  ‚îÇ
  ‚ñº
Nginx ‚îÄ‚îÄHTTP‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∂ PostService :3004
                      ‚îÇ
         ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê
         ‚îÇ            ‚îÇ                ‚îÇ
    PostgreSQL    Cassandra        MQTT Broker
    (media read,  (posts,          (post.created,
     restaurant   user_posts,       post.deleted)
     name read)   restaurant_posts)
```

On create, PostService reads media metadata and restaurant name from PostgreSQL, then writes to all three Cassandra tables in parallel.

---

## HTTP Endpoints

All endpoints are prefixed `/api/posts/` by Nginx.

---

### `POST /` üîí

Create a new post.

**Body:**
```json
{
  "media_id": "d3f1a2b4-...",
  "restaurant_id": "134469",
  "caption": "Best meal of my life.",
  "rating": "GOOD"
}
```

`restaurant_id` is optional. `rating` must be `"GOOD"` or `"BAD"`.

**Response `201`:**
```json
{
  "post_id": "e7c2b1a0-...",
  "user_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
  "username": "alice",
  "restaurant_id": "134469",
  "restaurant_name": "Le Gabriel - La R√©serve Paris",
  "media_type": "photo",
  "media_url": "/api/download/files/e7c2b1a0.jpg",
  "rating": "GOOD",
  "created_at": "2024-03-10T18:22:00Z"
}
```

> `thumbnail_url` and `caption` are stored in Cassandra but not included in the create response. Fetch the post with `GET /:id` to retrieve all fields.

**Errors:**

| Code | Reason |
|------|--------|
| 400  | `rating` is not `GOOD` or `BAD`, or `media_id` missing |
| 400  | `media_id` not found or belongs to a different user |
| 404  | `restaurant_id` not found in PostgreSQL |

On success, publishes a `post.created` MQTT event consumed by FeedService and StatsService.

---

### `GET /:id`

Fetch a single post by its UUID.

**Example:** `GET /api/posts/e7c2b1a0-...`

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "post_id": "e7c2b1a0-...",
  "user_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
  "username": "alice",
  "restaurant_id": "134469",
  "restaurant_name": "Le Gabriel - La R√©serve Paris",
  "media_id": "d3f1a2b4-...",
  "media_type": "photo",
  "media_url": "/api/download/files/e7c2b1a0.jpg",
  "thumbnail_url": null,
  "caption": "Best meal of my life.",
  "rating": "GOOD",
  "created_at": "2024-03-10T18:22:00Z"
}
```

**Response `404`:** `{ "error": "not found" }`

---

### `DELETE /:id` üîí

Delete a post. Only the post author can delete their own post.
Publishes a `post.deleted` MQTT event so StatsService can decrement counters.

**Response `204`:** No content.

**Errors:**

| Code | Reason |
|------|--------|
| 403  | Authenticated user is not the post author |
| 404  | Post not found |

---

### `GET /user/:user_id`

List all posts by a user, newest first. Reads from the `user_posts` Cassandra table.

**Example:** `GET /api/posts/user/a1b2c3d4-...?limit=10`

**Query parameters:**

| Parameter | Default | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| `before`  | now     | Cursor: ISO 8601 timestamp ‚Äî return posts older than this |
| `limit`   | 20      | Max results (max 100) |

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "post_id": "e7c2b1a0-...",
      "user_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
      "username": null,
      "restaurant_id": "134469",
      "restaurant_name": "Le Gabriel - La R√©serve Paris",
      "media_id": null,
      "media_type": "photo",
      "media_url": "/api/download/files/e7c2b1a0.jpg",
      "thumbnail_url": null,
      "caption": "Best meal of my life.",
      "rating": "GOOD",
      "created_at": "2024-03-10T18:22:00Z"
    }
  ],
  "next_before": "2024-03-10T18:22:00Z"
}
```

Pass `?before=<next_before>` in the next request to get the following page. `next_before` is `null` when there are no more results.

---

### `GET /restaurant/:restaurant_id`

List all posts tagged to a restaurant, newest first. Reads from the `restaurant_posts` Cassandra table.

`:restaurant_id` is the Michelin `objectID` ‚Äî the same `VARCHAR(50)` primary key used in PostgreSQL `restaurants.id`.

**Example:** `GET /api/posts/restaurant/134469?limit=10`

**Query parameters:** same as `/user/:user_id`.

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "post_id": "e7c2b1a0-...",
      "user_id": "a1b2c3d4-...",
      "username": "alice",
      "restaurant_id": "134469",
      "restaurant_name": "Le Gabriel - La R√©serve Paris",
      "media_id": null,
      "media_type": "video",
      "media_url": "/api/download/files/e7c2b1a0.mp4",
      "thumbnail_url": "/api/download/files/e7c2b1a0_thumb.jpg",
      "caption": "Amazing tasting menu.",
      "rating": "GOOD",
      "created_at": "2024-03-09T12:10:00Z"
    }
  ],
  "next_before": "2024-03-09T12:10:00Z"
}
```

---

## Cassandra Tables

PostService writes to all three tables on every create/delete for O(1) reads:

| Table | Partition key | Use case |
|-------|--------------|----------|
| `posts` | `post_id` | Direct lookup by ID |
| `user_posts` | `user_id` | Profile page timeline |
| `restaurant_posts` | `restaurant_id` | Restaurant page feed |

All tables carry `rating` so the frontend never needs a second query to restaurant_stats.

---

## MQTT Events Published

| Topic          | Payload |
|----------------|---------|
| `post.created` | `{ "post_id", "restaurant_id", "rating", "user_id" }` |
| `post.deleted` | `{ "post_id", "restaurant_id", "rating" }` |

---

## Configuration

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://admin:changeme@localhost:5432/hackmichelin
CASSANDRA_NODES=localhost:9042
HTTP_ADDR=0.0.0.0:3004
JWT_SECRET=changeme
MQTT_HOST=localhost
MQTT_PORT=1883
MQTT_CLIENT_ID=post-service
RUST_LOG=info
```

---

## Local Development

```bash
cp .env.example .env
cargo run
```

